{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender with no prior criminal history and has demonstrated some accountability by partially paying back the embezzled $25,000. However, as an accountant, they held a fiduciary duty and abused a position of trust, which constitutes a serious offense. The outburst by the courtroom spectator carries no legal weight and is disregarded. Balancing the mitigating factors of the partial restitution and clean record against the gravity of the white-collar theft, a split-sentence or short period of incarceration is appropriate. Therefore, the defendant is sentenced to 6 months of incarceration, followed by probation and full restitution requirements.",
  "verdict": 6
}
